article.description: — Duncan Powell had a triple-double to power Sacramento State to a 100-45 victory over Bethesda University on Thursday night.
article.headline: Powell has triple-double as Sacramento State routs Bethesda 100-45
article.linkText: Powell has triple-double as Sacramento State routs Bethesda 100-45
article.story: SACRAMENTO, Calif. -- — Duncan Powell had a triple-double to power Sacramento State to a 100-45 victory over Bethesda University on Thursday night. Powell finished with 13 points, 15 rebounds and 10 assists for the Hornets (3-8). Zee Hamoda added 14 points and five rebounds. Alex Kovatchev was 5 of 10 shooting (2 for 5 from 3-point range) to finish with 12 points. Stephen Perry led the way for the Flames with 24 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
